3.4 Implementation Details
Swin UNETR is implemented using PyTorch3 and MONAI4 and trained on a DGX-1 cluster with 8 NVIDIA V100 GPUs. Table 1 details the conï¬gurations of Swin UNETR architecture, number of parameters and FLOPs. The learning rate is set to 0.0008. We normalize all input images to have zero mean and unit standard deviation according to non-zero voxels. Random patches of 128 Ã— 128 Ã— 128 were cropped from 3D image volumes during training. We apply a random axis mirror ï¬‚ip with a probability of 0.5 for all 3 axes. Additionally, we
